body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Kenneth Scott and I am from TopCar Technologies. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great to meet you, Alexis. Can you please provide me with your date of birth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my date of birth is one nine eight five, July eleven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Alexis. Could you also share with me your telephone number for contact purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my telephone number is five five five, three two one, four four four four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Alexis. We will ensure it is kept secure. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, Kenneth, that's all for now. Thank you for your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Alexis. Thank you for your time and have a great day!
